Brazil  will provide as much as 3
billion reais ($1.5 billion) in grants and loans to fund
research into renewable energy.  The Inova Energia program will help companies commercialize
technology including solar power and energy-efficient vehicles,
Brazilâ€™s development bank Banco Nacional de Desenvolvimento
